    <etym xml:lang="ru">К <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>palāša-</w><gloss><q>листва</q></gloss></mentioned> (%ibælas%i — ‘дерево с
        листвой’ в противоположность <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd"/>?) Начальное %ib%i (вместо
        %if%i) ставит трудности; ср., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bycæw"/> (←
        %ipat%i-%ičaw%i-). Возможно и кавказское происхождение; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><lang/><w>bala</w><gloss><q>куст</q></gloss></mentioned>. К осетинскому примыкает
            <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>balas</w><gloss><q>салазки из молодых
                    деревьев для транспортировки сена с гор</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">To <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>palāša-</w><gloss><q>foliage</q></gloss></mentioned> (%ibælas%i — ‘tree
        with leaves’ as opposed to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd"/>?) The initial %ib%i (instead
        of %if%i) creats difficulties; cf., however, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bycæw"/> (←
        %ipat%i-%ičaw%i-). The Caucuasian origin is also possible; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><lang/><w>bala</w><gloss><q>bush</q></gloss></mentioned>. The following words are
        close to the Ossetic one: <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"
                    ><lang/><w>balas</w><gloss><q>sled made of young trees for transporting hay from
                    the mountains</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
